<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOVIET, EAST GERMAN APOLOGIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
It's remarkable and long overdue that East Germany openly acknowledges and 
apologizes for the horrors it perpetrated against Jews and others during the 
Nazi era. 
</P>
<P>
I wonder if it will ever be possible for our own country to officially 
acknowledge and apologize for the horrors we visited on the blacks brought as 
slaves from Africa, the destruction of the Indians, and the conquest of 
northern Mexico. 
</P>
<P>
We have begun to make restitution to the Japanese unjustly interned during 
World War II -- also along delayed and still blocked. Can we now go a step 
farther and do the same for the other victims of American history? 
</P>
<P>
LORNE H. WARD 
</P>
<P>
Garden Grove 
</P>
