<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: DUARTE TO TEST STATE'S NEW WELLNESS GUIDE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The city of Duarte, whose motto is "City of Health," has been selected by the 
state as the testing ground for a new Wellness Guide. 
</P>
<P>
A prototype of the guide, developed by the Office of Prevention of the state 
Department of Mental Health and UC Berkeley, was introduced Wednesday at a 
public health conference in Los Angeles. 
</P>
<P>
Duarte is to start distributing the guides on June 9. 
</P>
<P>
Produced by the School of Public Health at UC Berkeley, the resource guide 
covers a broad range of health-related topics, including pregnancy, child care, 
physical fitness and aging. The four-year program has a budget of $600,000, 
state officials said. 
</P>
<P>
Duarte was chosen because of its involvement in the "Healthy Cities Project," 
introduced last year to promote community health projects. 
</P>
</TEXT>
