<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURA COUNTY NEWS ROUNDUP: THOUSAND OAKS; 
</P>
<P>
CORONER SAYS MAN COMMITTED SUICIDE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CAROL WATSON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Ventura County coroner's office said Wednesday that a Thousand Oaks man 
found dead in a truck at the bottom of a ravine in Ventura had committed 
suicide. 
</P>
<P>
The man, Joseph Portao, 71, was reported missing by his wife five weeks ago. 
The body was found Monday after nearby residents spotted the truck. 
</P>
<P>
Portao had deliberately driven the truck off of a little-used road at the top 
of Kalorama Street and plunged 400 feet to his death, Deputy Coroner James 
Wingate said. 
</P>
<P>
Portao died from chest injuries and had been dead for about three weeks, 
Wingate said. CAROL WATSON 
</P>
</TEXT>
