<HEADLINE>
<P>
MAN FOUND SLAIN IN VAN NUYS ALLEY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 43-year-old Culver City man was found shot to death in a Van Nuys alley, and 
investigators had no clues to the motive for the slaying, Los Angeles police 
reported Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
Police were called to an alley behind the 6600 block of Hayvenhurst Avenue at 
8:45 p.m. Tuesday after residents reported hearing gunshots, Lt. Warren Knowles 
said. They found James Henry Atkinson sprawled on the ground behind an 
apartment building. 
</P>
<P>
Atkinson had been shot in the upper body. Police have been unable to determine 
what he was doing in the area or why he was shot. 
</P>
