<HEADLINE>
<P>
HIGH SCHOOL ROUNDUP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In other Avocado League games: 
</P>
<P>
San Marcos 9, Oceanside 1 -- Justin Woodart hit a grand slam in the fourth to 
extend San Marcos' lead to 8-1 in the fourth over No. 9 Oceanside (16-7, 4-2). 
Aaron Cassidy pitched a six hitter and retired eight of the last nine batters 
for San Marcos (9-9-1, 3-3). 
</P>
<P>
San Pasqual 6, Ramona 4 -- Tim Young came on in the fourth inning, pitched 
three and two-thirds innings and struck out six. Teammate Dave Goss hit his 
first home run for San Pasqual (7-9-1, 4-1). 
</P>
<P>
Grossmont 3-A League 
</P>
<P>
Helix 4, Monte Vista 1 -- Eric Nicholson (8-0) struck out 10 as visiting Helix 
(12-7-1, 1-1) upset fifth-ranked Monte Vista (14-8, 1-2). 
</P>
<P>
Granite Hills 20, Mount Miguel 0 -- Granite Hills (14-7-1, 1-1) scored in all 
but the fourth and got some heavy hitting from Jim Fenn (four for five, three 
RBIs, including a double and a triple) and Shane Spencer (three for five, seven 
RBIs). Mount Miguel fell to 4-17, 1-2. 
</P>
<P>
Grossmont 2-A League 
</P>
<P>
Grossmont 6, West Hills 4 -- Center fielder Lenny Van Every extended his 
consecutive game hitting streak to 20 with an RBI single in the fifth. Van 
Every's only hitless game was in Grossmont's opener. Jim Earley went two for 
three, including a two-run homer, and drove in two runs for second-ranked 
Grossmont (19-2, 2-0). West Hills is 3-16, 0-3. 
</P>
<P>
Palomar League 
</P>
<P>
Mt. Carmel 3, Vista 1 -- Matt Miller's solo home run in the sixth started a 
late surge for third-ranked Mt. Carmel (17-3, 7-0). Vista is 8-11-1, 2-4-1. 
</P>
<P>
Poway 12, Rancho Buena Vista 2 -- Robbie Plarski hit a two-run homer and Poway 
(13-5-1, 5-2) scored seven runs in the sixth inning to defeat RBV (9-10-1, 
4-3). Plarski had two hits and three RBIs. 
</P>
<P>
Fallbrook 15, Torrey Pines 9 -- After Torrey Pines scored seven runs in the 
second, Fallbrook (9-8, 4-3) came back with 13 in the third, during which 19 
batters stepped to the plate. Matt Dunlop hit a three-run home run, his fifth, 
and Jose Gonzales hit a grand slam. 
</P>
<P>
Orange Glen 11, San Dieguito 2 -- Scott Coleman pitched a one-hitter and hit 
two three-run home runs for Orange Glen (13-8, 4-3). San Dieguito is 1-5-1, 
2-17-1. 
</P>
<P>
Nonleague 
</P>
<P>
El Capitan 11, El Cajon 0 -- David Rios (6-1) pitched his first shutout of the 
year, striking out five and allowing no walks for El Capitan (14-7). 
</P>
<P>
Boys' Track and Field 
</P>
<P>
La Jolla 71, University City 64 -- La Jolla won the Western League championship 
with its ninth consecutive victory this season and its 37th in a row dating 
back to 1985. The meet wasn't decided until the mile relay. University City's 
Jerome Price, national long jump leader and one of the county's top sprinters, 
was held from the long jump to keep fresh for the relay, but it didn't work. La 
Jolla anchor Steve Azcona inherited a 30-yard advantage and maintained it over 
Price with a 51.7 final leg. 
</P>
