<HEADLINE>
<P>
SPORTS ET CETERA: CHARGERS SIGN FIVE FREE AGENTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Chargers announced the signings of five free agents on Wednesday: 
</P>
<P>
Willie Davis, cornerback, Southern Illinois (5-feet-10, 185); Wayne Dickson, 
inside linebacker, Oklahoma (6-3 253); Derick Dednam, defensive end, North 
Caroline State (6-2 1/2, 255); Tony Gunn, defensive lineman, UNLV (6-5, 310) 
and Wendell Jones, wide receiver, Grambling (5-10, 175). 
</P>
<P>
BASEBALL 
</P>
<P>
NAIA school Azusa Pacific dealt host U.S. International a 16-6 loss, finishing 
things off in the ninth with six runs. 
</P>
<P>
USIU fell to 12-36-1. Azusa is 28-10. 
</P>
<P>
The Master's routed Point Loma Nazarene, 13-6, in a Golden State Athletic 
Conference game. PLNC got two home runs, the first with the bases empty by Brad 
Harden and the second a three-run homer by Mark Ratekin. 
</P>
<P>
WOMEN'S TENNIS 
</P>
<P>
Laura Richards of Vista High has signed a letter of intent at USD, Torera Coach 
Sherri Stephens announced. Richards won the 1989 national hardcourt doubles 
championship and is ranked No. 3 nationally in doubles and 32nd in singles. 
Julie McKeon, the Illinois state singles champion, and Kara Brady, a two-time 
Missouri state champion, also signed. 
</P>
<P>
WOMEN'S VOLLEYBALL 
</P>
<P>
Myles Gabel, 33, was named assistant to Rudy Suwara at San Diego State. Gabel 
had a 59-39 record in three years at New Mexico State. He fills a position 
vacated by Sue Hegerle, who is now USD's coach. 
</P>
