<HEADLINE>
<P>
BROSE, GOFFREDO ON NEW SCHOOL'S STAFF 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARTIN HENDERSON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Rancho Bernardo High School will have at least two coaches with section 
championships on their resumes when it opens in the fall. 
</P>
<P>
The Broncos have named Peggy Brose the girls' basketball coach and Tony 
Goffredo the boys' and girls' tennis coach. 
</P>
<P>
Brose led Mt. Carmel to the section title in 1988 and again this year. Goffredo 
coached Mt. Carmel's boys to a tennis championship in 1989 and has reached the 
finals three of the past four years. 
</P>
<P>
Also named were Poway assistant Chris Carter, who will coach the boys' 
basketball team, and Jeff Ukrainetz, who leaves Mt. Carmel to head the Rancho 
Bernardo swim program. MARTIN HENDERSON 
</P>
</TEXT>
