<HEADLINE>
<P>
EARNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Goodyear Tire &amp; Rubber Co.: The company said first-quarter profit totaled 
$20.9 million, down 78% from the same period last year. Sales rose slightly to 
$2.7 billion. The world's largest rubber maker, based in Akron, Ohio, blamed 
pricing competition, cutbacks in North American vehicle production and higher 
costs for advertising and wages. 
</P>
