<HEADLINE>
<P>
PEOPLE: NATIONAL MERCANTILE NAMES PRESIDENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
William T. Hughes has been named president and chief operating officer of 
National Mercantile Bancorp in Los Angeles and its Mercantile National Bank 
subsidiary. 
</P>
<P>
Hughes most recently was a senior vice president with Security Pacific National 
Bank. He succeeds Terry T. Tomich, who resigned earlier this month. 
</P>
<P>
National Mercantile is a business bank specializing increasingly in 
entertainment lending. A partnership affiliated with Creative Artists Agency, 
Hollywood's most influential talent agency, owns nearly 10% of National 
Mercantile. A separate stake of nearly 10% is owned by Breslauer, Jacobson, 
Rutman &amp; Sherman, one of the entertainment industry's top business 
management firms. 
</P>
</TEXT>
