<TEXT>
<P>
Birmingham High jumped to a four-run lead and held on to beat visiting Van 
Nuys, 5-3, Wednesday for its 10th consecutive victory, the longest winning 
streak in Wayne Sink's 12 seasons as Birmingham's coach. 
</P>
<P>
Jason Mansfield and Josh Brown combined to limit Van Nuys to four hits in the 
Mid-Valley League game. Mansfield (4-3) struck out seven before Brown came on 
in the seventh to earn his first save of the season. 
</P>
<P>
Catcher Seth Rosenzweig drove in two runs. Birmingham (15-5-1, 9-4 in league 
play) scored five runs on four hits. 
</P>
<P>
