<P>
ROMEO TAKES LEAD INTO LPBT FINALS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By AP 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
FAYETTEVILLE, Ga. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Robin Romeo of Van Nuys, seeking her first title of the year, earned the 
top-seeded position Wednesday night for the finals of the $35,000 Ladies Pro 
Bowlers Tour Greater Atlanta Open. 
</P>
<P>
Romeo held a 244-pin margin over Stacy Rider heading into tonight's finals. 
</P>
<P>
Romeo, a five-time champion in 1989 when she earned a record $113,750 and was 
named Bowler of the Year, has not finished higher than 16th in the LPBT's first 
six tournaments of 1990. Romeo, a 12-time career winner, averaged 209 while 
winning 19 of her 24 matches for a 42-game total of 9,359 pins. Rider, with 
9,105 pins, and Jeri Edwards, at 9,019, are each trying for their first career 
title. 
</P>
