<TEXT>
<P>
'Nasty' Found Obscene in Ohio: "As Nasty as They Wanna Be," the sexually 
explicit album by the Miami-based rap group 2 Live Crew, is too nasty for 
Cincinnati. According to a decision reached Wednesday by the Hamilton County 
Vice Squad, the controversial million-selling album was deemed a violation of 
Ohio obscenity statutes. 
</P>
<P>
When police visited the five stores in the county that carried the album, only 
one of them had the uncensored version. The store promptly removed the album at 
the police's request. There was no hearing or court proceeding involved in 
naming the album obscene, only a decision by Sherriff Simon Leif, who was 
involved in the recent controversy over the Robert Mapplethorpe exhibit in 
Cincinnati, and the vice squad. BETH KLEID 
