<P>
WESTSIDE DIGEST: CULVER CITY; 
</P>
<P>
NINE NEW RECYCLING SITES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Newspaper, cans and bottles can be dropped off at nine new recycling sites in 
Culver City. 
</P>
<P>
The sites, set up by the city, will take glass bottles and jars, aluminum and 
tin cans, plastic bottles, and newspapers. 
</P>
<P>
The materials do not have to be separated. The drop-off spots are part of a 
recycling plan that the city is developing in an effort to reduce by 25% its 
waste going to landfills. 
</P>
<P>
Recycling locations are: City Hall, Duquesne Avenue and Culver Boulevard; 
National Guard Armory, 10808 Culver Blvd.; Tellefson Park, Washington Place and 
Tilden Avenue; Culver West Park, 4162 Wade Ave.; Culver-Palms Methodist Church, 
4464 Sepulveda Blvd.; Lindberg Park, 11020 Ocean Drive; Sunkist Park, Port Road 
and Dawes Avenue; Culver Park, Duquesne Avenue and Jefferson Boulevard, and 
McManus Park, 3459 McManus Ave. 
</P>
