<HEADLINE>
<P>
NOTEBOOK; 
</P>
<P>
COLTS SELECT AREA PRODUCTS GRANT, SCHULTZ 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GARY KLEIN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Indianapolis Colts selected two former Glendale-area players in the NFL 
draft this week. 
</P>
<P>
Stanford defensive back Alan Grant, who played at St. Francis High, and USC 
offensive lineman Bill Schultz, a former junior college All-American at 
Glendale College, were taken in the fourth round by Indianapolis. 
</P>
<P>
CS Fullerton running back Michael Pringle, who attended but never played at 
Glendale, was taken by Atlanta in the sixth round. 
</P>
<P>
Special competition: More than 350 athletes from the San Gabriel Valley will 
participate in a Special Olympics regional qualifying meet Saturday at 
Occidental. The competition will include track and field, swimming, soccer, 
basketball, weightlifting and gymnastics. Participants can advance to the state 
meet at UCLA this summer. 
</P>
<P>
On the road: Driver David Kudrave of La Canada finished 10th in the 100-mile 
American Racing Series event at Long Beach on Sunday, winning $1,400. 
</P>
<P>
Kudrave, 24, was competing in the first of 14 ARS events, which are contested 
in Wildcat V-6 Buicks with 450-horsepower engines. 
</P>
<P>
Chuck Kendall of La Canada drove a Ford Mustang to a fifth-place finish in the 
IMSA GT race Saturday and collected $2,500. 
</P>
<P>
On track: Glendale (10-1), which has won 14 Western State Conference track 
titles in 15 years, is in second place in the men's division, behind 
Bakersfield, entering the conference finals Friday. The Glendale women (7-2) 
trail Moorpark (9-0) and Bakersfield (8-1). Results from the finals and 
head-to-head competition determine the conference champion. 
</P>
<P>
On track II: The Occidental track team defeated Whittier last Saturday to 
conclude its Southern California Intercollegiate Athletic Conference schedule 
at 6-0. 
</P>
<P>
The Tigers, under Coach Bill Harvey, can clinch the SCIAC title by sweeping the 
conference championship meet that begins Friday at Redlands. 
</P>
<P>
Kirby Lee contributed to this notebook. 
</P>
</TEXT>
