<HEADLINE>
<P>
MARINA SHERIFF'S STATION CHIEF NAMED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Los Angeles County Sheriff's Department has appointed Clarence R. Chapman, 
a 24-year veteran of the department, as captain of the Marina del Rey station. 
</P>
<P>
As captain of the Marina station, which covers the marina area and the 
communities of View Park, Windsor Hills and Ladera Heights, Chapman will be in 
charge of 72 deputies, including 15 deputies working the harbor boat patrol. 
</P>
<P>
Chapman, 43, who has been meeting with community groups since his appointment, 
described the area as diverse. 
</P>
<P>
"It has the marina, which is a high-density area with condominiums and concerns 
about traffic and development, and the residential communities of View Park, 
Ladera Heights and Windsor Hills, where the concerns are more about safe 
streets and safe schools," he said. 
</P>
<P>
Chapman has held several positions since joining the Sheriff's Department in 
1966. As a sergeant, he was a manager of a program that tracked career 
criminals. More recently, he served as a lieutenant in the narcotic bureau in 
Whittier. 
</P>
<P>
"We targeted underground drug smuggling and distribution operations involving 
rock cocaine, primarily in the mid-city," he said. "This (new assignment) is 
much less job-specific and very much less stressful. The drug problem is very 
frustrating because no matter how much effort we put in, it seems to escalate." 
</P>
<P>
Born in Columbus, Ohio, he moved to Los Angeles in 1960. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Appointment 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
