39 'BOAT PEOPLE' ARE RESCUED BY WARSHIP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
MANILA 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A U.S. warship picked up 39 Vietnamese "boat people" adrift in the South China 
Sea, a U.S. Navy spokesman said Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
The refugees included 15 children, the youngest a 1-year-old baby. The engine 
