<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP BASEBALL ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
KATELLA BEATS CYPRESS FOR 8TH VICTORY IN ROW 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Chris Drummond pitched a complete-game victory, but his scoreless inning streak 
ended at 27 2/3 as Katella High School defeated Cypress, 8-3, in an Empire 
League game at Boysen Park in Anaheim. 
</P>
<P>
Cypress scored two runs in the fifth with the help of a two-out bloop single 
off Drummond (6-0). 
</P>
<P>
Jess Evans hit a two-run home run, just to the right of the 400-foot sign in 
center field in the first, and Dennis Briggs had two hits and two RBIs for 
Katella (16-4, 7-3). The Knights have won eight in a row, but are still three 
games behind first-place Esperanza. 
</P>
<P>
In other Empire League games: 
</P>
<P>
Esperanza 8, Loara 3 -- Erickson Dumual had two hits and scored a run and Dan 
Redington had two hits and three RBIs for host Esperanza (16-4, 10-0). Joe Foss 
(5-0) pitched four innings for the victory and Keith McDonald pitched three 
innings for his fifth save. 
</P>
<P>
Los Alamitos 7, El Dorado 3 -- Doug Kieck hit a three-run home run in the sixth 
inning to give the Griffins (9-11-1, 6-4) a 4-2 lead at El Dorado. Todd 
Gragnano pitched six innings, striking out six, to get the victory. Gar Vallone 
had two doubles for El Dorado (11-10, 3-7). 
</P>
<P>
In the Garden Grove League: 
</P>
<P>
Pacifica 1, Santiago 0 (8 innings) -- Chris Castellano had a one-out squeeze 
bunt in the eighth to score Chris Shockley with the winning run for host 
Pacifica (11-10, 4-5). Winning pitcher Rob Toth (6-4) pitched a two-hitter with 
nine strikeouts. 
</P>
<P>
Kennedy 13, Bolsa Grande 3 -- Kennedy scored eight runs in the first inning 
with the help of three hits and eight Bolsa Grande errors at Bolsa Grande. 
</P>
<P>
Scott Wood, Rod Rosales and Bryan Walsh had two hits each for Kennedy (11-11, 
6-3). 
</P>
<P>
Garden Grove 5, Los Amigos 1 -- Shawn Zingali (4-3) pitched a four-hitter, 
striking out seven, to lead host Garden Grove (7-9, 4-5). Rob Wursthorn had 
three hits and two RBIs, and Joe Aguirre had two triples and scored twice. 
</P>
<P>
In the Orange League: 
</P>
<P>
Magnolia 4, Anaheim 0 -- Chad Phillips (4-2) pitched a four-hitter and had 
eight strikeouts for visiting Magnolia (7-8, 6-4). Tony Treul had three hits 
and two RBIs. Mauricio Hernandez drove in the other runs. 
</P>
<P>
