<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFCASE: RETAIL/TOURISM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Chris Woodyard, Times staff writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Economy Hotel: Marriott Corp. has already dotted the county with hotels 
offering a range of room rates. And, on Wednesday, the giant lodging chain 
dedicated its newest hotel, the 135-room Fairfield Inn in Buena Park. 
</P>
<P>
The Fairfield Inn is the economy version of the Marriott group. For prices 
starting at $31.95 a night, weary travelers get few extras: For example, the 
rooms offer no travel-size shampoo or bubble bath. The hotel has only one 
meeting room and no attached restaurant. 
</P>
<P>
But the Fairfield Inn, on Orangethorpe Avenue near Knott Avenue, does have a 
swimming pool. Although it may sound closer to the Motel 6 price range, 
Fairfield Inn spokeswoman Dee Dee Dochen said other Fairfield Inns around the 
country typically draw from budget-conscious travelers who want Marriott 
quality without Marriott prices. 
</P>
<P>
While new to Orange County, Fairfield Inns now has 50 locations around the 
nation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
