Orange County Life; Part N; Page 4; Column 1 
</P>
</SECTION>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, 'Once in Arden' Opens at SCR "Once in Arden" playwright Richard 
Hellensen, left, speaks with Jacquie Gray, director Martin Benson and Don Gray 
of Toshiba America Information Systems Inc. at a pre-curtain celebration Friday 
night at the Center Club to honor the three Toshiba America Companies of 
Southern California for underwriting the play's world premiere at South Coast 
Repertory's Mainstage. "Once in Arden," about one of Orange County's most noted 
residents, was one of the winners in the California Play Festival. The play 
leads off CalFest 1990, which will present the works of seven California 
playwrights. ROD BOREN / For The Times 
</P>
