<HEADLINE>
<P>
PACIFICARE, MAXICARE BREAK OFF TALKS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LESLIE BERKMAN, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A bid by Cypress-based PacifiCare Health Systems Inc., to expand in Southern 
California by acquiring bankrupt Maxicare Health Plans Inc. of Los Angeles ran 
aground Wednesday after negotiations broke off. 
</P>
<P>
In separate statements, both health maintenance organizations confirmed that 
the talks ended abruptly and that no further discussions are contemplated on 
PacifiCare's preliminary offer. 
</P>
<P>
Neither company would disclose details of the offer, which was made public last 
Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
A merger would have increased PacifiCare's membership to 956,000 by adding 
Maxicare's approximately 320,000 members. More important, it would have boosted 
PacifiCare's already large presence in Southern California. 
</P>
</TEXT>
