<HEADLINE>
<P>
GREAT NORMAND SCORES VICTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEW YORK 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Great Normand took the lead entering the stretch and then held to win by a head 
over Phantom Breeze in the $36,000 Shelter Bay Stakes for older horses at 
Aqueduct. 
</P>
<P>
The win was the first in three starts this year for Great Normand, who is owned 
by Victor Resk. He covered 1 1/16 miles on a turf course rated "good" in 1:46 
2/5 and earned $21,600. 
</P>
<P>
Great Normand, ridden by J.C. Ferrer and carrying 119 pounds, returned $28.20, 
$8 and $6.40. Phantom Breeze paid $2.80 and $2.40 and Kate's Valentine, who was 
another 4 3/4 lengths back in third in the nine-horse field, returned $4.20 to 
show. 
</P>
