<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN GABRIEL VALLEY DIGEST: SOUTH PASADENA; 
</P>
<P>
FIERRO SELECTED AS MAYOR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The City Council unanimously chose Evelyn Fierro as mayor and Dick Richards as 
mayor pro tem. 
</P>
<P>
Fierro, 41, a former television news journalist who last fall started a public 
relations firm, is in her first term on the council. 
</P>
<P>
She was elected to the four-year position in 1988. She also is running as a 
Democrat for the 42nd District Assembly seat held by Republican Richard 
Mountjoy of Arcadia. 
</P>
<P>
A retired FBI agent, Richards, 68, is a businessman. He won his seat in a 
special election last fall. 
</P>
<P>
Unlike many other San Gabriel Valley cities, South Pasadena selects its mayor 
and mayor pro tem once a year, rather than allowing the positions to rotate 
among five council members during a four-year period. 
</P>
</TEXT>
