<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTHLAND; 
</P>
<P>
NO ONE GETS ALL SIX IN LOTTERY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and wire service reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A $4.76-million jackpot went unclaimed today as no one correctly guessed all 
six winning numbers picked Wednesday night in the California Lottery's "Lotto 
6-49" game, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
The jackpot will roll over to an estimated $10 million for Saturday night's 
drawing. 
</P>
<P>
Seven players picked five numbers plus the bonus number. Each won $182,859, 
dividing a prize pool of $1.3 million. 
</P>
<P>
There were 207 tickets with five of six numbers, each winning $3,185, and 
12,447 ticket-holders will get $48 for holding four of six numbers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
