PACT OKD ON JOINT EURO-COPTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
PARIS 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
France, West Germany, Italy and the Netherlands have agreed to build a military 
helicopter together, the French Defense Ministry said today. 
</P>
<P>
The ministry said in a statement that West German and French defense ministers 
agreed to the project during a two-day Franco-German summit which ended today. 
</P>
<P>
It said the NH-90 transport helicopter will be built in cooperation with Italy 
and the Netherlands. German participation depends on approval from its 
parliament, the statement added. 
</P>
<P>
France's state-owned Aerospatiale and West Germany's Messerschmitt have agreed 
to pool their helicopter operations to build the NH-90. Italy's Agusta and the 
Dutch Fokker companies will be the other firms involved. 
</P>
