<P>
UNIVERSITY TO HONOR TOM T. HALL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
MURFREESBORO, Tenn. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A $1.25-million chair in creative writing will be established at Middle 
Tennessee State University to honor singer, songwriter and author Tom T. Hall, 
known as "the Storyteller." 
</P>
<P>
"This is the highest honor that's ever come my way," said Hall, who wrote the 
country music hit "Harper Valley PTA" and recently published his sixth book and 
second novel, "Spring Hill, Tennessee." 
</P>
<P>
Hall has been a guest lecturer at the school, which announced the chair last 
week. 
</P>
<P>
The chair will be endowed by matching public and private contributions. 
</P>
