<P>
THE SIDELINES; 
</P>
<P>
GRAZIANO OUT OF INTENSIVE CARE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEW YORK 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Former world middleweight champion Rocky Graziano was removed from the 
intensive care unit today at New York Hospital Cornell Medical Center, where he 
is recovering from a stroke. 
</P>
<P>
A hospital spokesman said that Graziano remains in serious condition but that 
his vital signs are stable. 
</P>
<P>
Graziano, 67, had the stroke April 8, and this is the third time in seven 
months that he has been hospitalized. 
</P>
<P>
Last October, Graziano was treated at Lenox Hill Hospital for mental and 
physical exhaustion. He had a heart attack last February and was hospitalized 
at the NYU Medical Center. 
</P>
<P>
In his 11-year professional career, Graziano knocked out 52 of 83 opponents. 
</P>
