146 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
TRAFFIC, TRAFFIC AND MORE TRAFFIC . . . 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Residents say traffic is the biggest problem facing North County, according to 
a recent Times Poll. More than growth, more than the environment, more than 
drugs or crime. 
</P>
<P>
North County Focus wants to address some of those concerns in upcoming issues. 
But first, we would like to hear more about them. 
</P>
<P>
What is the most vexing commuting experience you have faced in North County? 
Which are the worst roads? What questions do you want answered about commuting 
-- by car or public transportation? 
</P>
<P>
Does it burn you up when you see a single commuter driving in the car-pool 
lanes? Do you wonder why Interstate 5 backs up so badly during the Del Mar Fair 
and racing seasons? 
</P>
<P>
Write to us about your experiences and your questions. We will try to address 
them. Send your letters to: 
</P>
<P>
North County Focus Traffic Survey 
</P>
<P>
400 S. Melrose Drive, Suite 108 
</P>
<P>
Vista, Calif. 92083 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
